  "text": "and T perc c versus 1/ C p for various liquids. Crossover temperatures from activated to non-activated dynamics were determined by using Stickel plot analysis [CITATION_1] . The experimental crossover temperatures for 21 substances obtained in this way by Novikov and Sokolov [CITATION_2] are plotted in the figure along with the RFOT prediction. Some of the outliers are polymers for which other slowing effects compound simple RFOT results. Uncertainty in T K for very strong liquids is probably a source of discrepancy between the theory and experimental results for these latter substances. We also plot (T c − T g )/T g in Fig. 2b . According to RFOT theory, the entropy at",
